# Adaptation Plan

## Intent
Enhances the GC dangling artifacts functionality to support targeted deletion of specific stale indices (identified by UUIDs) during resize operations from failed prior attempts, falling back to full scan for empty lists; updates the planner to reference the new full-GC request constant; adds new version constants for compatibility.

## Per-file changes

### server/src/main/java/io/crate/execution/ddl/tables/TransportGCDanglingArtifacts.java
Modify the `execute` method in the `DDLClusterStateTaskExecutor` to handle targeted index deletion if `indexUUIDs()` is non-empty (deleting the matching indices directly), otherwise proceed with the existing full dangling indices scan logic. This enables efficient cleanup of specific stale resize artifacts without full scans.

```diff
        Metadata metadata = currentState.metadata();

        Set<Index> danglingIndicesToDelete = new HashSet<>();
---
        Metadata metadata = currentState.metadata();

        List<String> targetUUIDs = gcDanglingArtifactsRequest.indexUUIDs();
        if (!targetUUIDs.isEmpty()) {
            Set<Index> indicesToDelete = new HashSet<>();
            for (String uuid : targetUUIDs) {
                IndexMetadata indexMetadata = metadata.index(uuid);
                if (indexMetadata != null) {
                    indicesToDelete.add(indexMetadata.getIndex());
                }
            }
            if (indicesToDelete.isEmpty()) {
                return currentState;
            }
            return deleteIndexService.deleteIndices(currentState, indicesToDelete);
        }

        Set<Index> danglingIndicesToDelete = new HashSet<>();
```

### server/src/main/java/io/crate/planner/GCDanglingArtifactsPlan.java
Update the GC execution to use the new `GCDanglingArtifactsRequest.ALL` constant (empty list) which triggers full dangling scan in the updated transport logic.

```diff
        dependencies.client().execute(TransportGCDanglingArtifacts.ACTION, GCDanglingArtifactsRequest.INSTANCE)
            .whenComplete(listener);
---
        dependencies.client().execute(TransportGCDanglingArtifacts.ACTION, GCDanglingArtifactsRequest.ALL)
            .whenComplete(listener);
```

### server/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/Version.java
Add new version constants `V_6_0_4` and `V_6_1_1` with snapshot flags for internal compatibility, positioned after existing 5.x versions.

```diff
    public static final Version V_5_6_5 = new Version(8_06_05_99, false, org.apache.lucene.util.Version.LUCENE_9_9_1);

    public static final Version V_5_7_0 = new Version(8_07_00_99, false, org.apache.lucene.util.Version.LUCENE_9_10_0);
---
    public static final Version V_5_6_5 = new Version(8_06_05_99, false, org.apache.lucene.util.Version.LUCENE_9_9_1);
    public static final Version V_6_0_4 = new Version(9_00_04_99, true, org.apache.lucene.util.Version.LUCENE_10_2_2);
    public static final Version V_6_1_1 = new Version(9_01_01_99, true, org.apache.lucene.util.Version.LUCENE_10_2_2);

    public static final Version V_5_7_0 = new Version(8_07_00_99, false, org.apache.lucene.util.Version.LUCENE_9_10_0);
```

## No-change files
- server/src/main/java/io/crate/execution/ddl/tables/GCDanglingArtifactsRequest.java: Already adapted with `indexUUIDs()` and `ALL` constant (prior hunk accepted)

## Risk notes
- Targeted deletion in `TransportGCDanglingArtifacts` assumes provided UUIDs correspond to dangling indices; misuse could delete active table indices (mitigated by resize-specific usage).
- `LUCENE_10_2_2` availability unconfirmed in target Lucene version; may require fallback to latest available (e.g., `LUCENE_9_10_0`).
- No dropped hunks; all prior accepted edits carried forward.
